.\" termin.al-name: man
.\" termin.al-usage: man <command>
.\" termin.al-summary: Show a command manual.
.TH MAN 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
man \- Show a command manual.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
man <command>
man -P vim <command>
man --pager=vim <command>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reads a project-authored section-1 manual for a registered command. Ordinary mode prints the generated text; Vim mode opens the same text in a keyboard pager.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -P vim
Open the selected manual in the Vim manpager.
.TP
.B --pager=vim
Open the selected manual in the Vim manpager.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ man grep
$ man -P vim grep
$ man --pager=vim pane
.fi
.SH NOTES
Manual sources are roff files generated to checked UTF-8 artifacts during the production build. Aliases resolve through the command registry to the canonical manual.
.SH SEE ALSO
help(1), less(1)
